.TH "snd_seq_kernel_client_ctl" 9 "snd_seq_kernel_client_ctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_seq_kernel_client_ctl \- operate a command for a client with data in kernel space.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_seq_kernel_client_ctl
.BI "(int clientid "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmd "  ","
.BI "void *arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clientid" 12
A numerical ID for a client.
.IP "cmd" 12
An ioctl(2) command for ALSA sequencer operation.
.IP "arg" 12
A pointer to data in kernel space.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Against its name, both kernel/application client can be handled by this
kernel API. A pointer of 'arg' argument should be in kernel space.
.SH "RETURN"
0 at success. Negative error code at failure.
